status: MARC21-007: Configuration of playback channels of video
Configuration of intended playback channels for the sound portion of a videorecording.

definition (en): More than one configuration of playback channels for the sound portion is available on a single videorecording.
scope note (en): An example would be a tape with both monaural and stereophonic sound tracks.

definition (en): Configured to be played back on one channel.
Videorecording has no sound or sound is on separate medium.
Configured to be played back on more than two channels.
scope note (en): Use for Dolby surround sound tracks and other multichannel techniques.

definition (en): Configured to be played back on two separate channels.
Configuration of playback channels for the sound portion of a videorecording is not known.

Configuration of playback channels other than mixed, monaural, not applicable
quadraphonic, multichannel, or surround, stereophonic.
